<subSubSection id="82D6B471727A2E5D67639BED73F66D5E" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph id="AAA24434053573AE7876D84A146CE59E" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="26FE791A60CB874759B4463359B961BA" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B2A236F27257477151FA06AF3328FC96" bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Leaf</emphasis>
collars often scabrous or hispidulous near the throat; ligules of middle cauline leaves 0.2-1.5 mm long, not decurrent, abaxially smooth or scabrous, upper margin scabrous or ciliolate or glabrous, apices truncate; sterile shoot blades frequently glabrous adaxially. 
<emphasis id="6453AFC7860E9AC6AA4B5C660377BA3F" bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Spikelet</emphasis>
rachilla internodes smooth, glabrous; lemma keels and marginal veins smooth or sparingly scabrous, glabrous or sparsely short villous to softly puberulent; palea keels glabrous, between keels glabrous. 
<emphasis id="DD67C0F948639D6FC65CA56C16990499" bold="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Lodicules</emphasis>
0.6-0.7 mm long, broadly lanceolate to ovate, with or without a brief lateral lobe from below the middle. 2 
<emphasis id="AC580FDB98BE7715EBE557F625B213EC" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">n</emphasis>
= 28, 28+II.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="32D2255D37884D424D3C700B8D1516A5" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="1AF76F8D0F90DEF72C1A97BAB27B58AB" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6BC15EFD19025799F186565AFBC38019" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">The subspecies is endemic to southeastern Arizona, southwestern New Mexico, USA, and the northern Sierra Madre Occidental of Mexico (Chihuahua, Sonora).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
